                            <comment id="15437105" author="jamestaylor" created="Thu, 25 Aug 2016 15:47:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;FYI, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=apurtell&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;apurtell&quot;&gt;Andrew Purtell&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=lhofhansl&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;lhofhansl&quot;&gt;Lars Hofhansl&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15440606" author="lhofhansl" created="Sat, 27 Aug 2016 03:51:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is client side of the scanning timing out, right?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15440633" author="lhofhansl" created="Sat, 27 Aug 2016 04:10:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;1.1 and later have &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-13090&quot; title=&quot;Progress heartbeats for long running scanners&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-13090&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-13090&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. In 0.98 there&apos;s no way other than increasing the rpc timeout as far as I know.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
